## Codegraph MCP (Go exploration)

When `.codegraph/` exists, prefer `user-codegraph` over ad-hoc Grep/Read loops for Go symbols. Full tool recipes and fallbacks: **codegraph-tools.md**.

Session habits:

1. **Confirm index** — `codegraph_status` with `projectPath` set to the repo root (this workspace has no default project).
2. **Orient** — `codegraph_files` on the package dir (e.g. `engine/collect`).
3. **Before editing a symbol** — `codegraph_search` → `codegraph_node` (pin with `file`/`line`) → `codegraph_callers` / `codegraph_callees` or `codegraph_impact` for refactors.
4. **`codegraph_explore` is unavailable** — use the four-tool recipe in codegraph-tools.md.

Fall back to Read, Grep, Glob for markdown, YAML/CI, string literals, concept search, or when the index is missing/stale.

## Collect workflow (interactive path)

For Survey → intent → engine → disk, follow **collect-request-flow.md**. Key convergence point: both `prof tui`/`prof ui` and `prof auto` call `collect.RunAuto` via `internal/app` — CLI/intent never import `engine/*` directly.

Quick "where to edit" anchors (details in collect-request-flow.md):

| Change | Start file |
| --- | --- |
| Survey prompts / advanced options | `cli/tui.go`, `cli/collect_preview.go` |
| Intent validation | `internal/intent/collect.go` |
| Benchmark discovery | `engine/collect/discovery.go` |
| `go test` argv / profile flags | `engine/collect/gotest.go`, `engine/tooling/catalog.go` |
| Profile processing / lenient / skip PNG | `engine/collect/profiles.go` |
| Per-function extracts / filters | `parser/`, `internal/config/filter.go` |
| Output paths / tag lifecycle | `internal/workspace/layout.go`, `engine/collect/layout.go` |

## Layering reminder

`cli`, `internal/tui`, and `internal/intent` → `internal/app` only → engines. Cross-boundary types live in `internal/app/dto.go`. See CODEBASE_DESIGN.md before adding imports that skip this boundary.
